{"id":842,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":842,"title":"Mene mene tekel upharsin","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mene mene tekel upharsin","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mene-mene-tekel-upharsin","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mene-mene-tekel-upharsin.t1","order":".000.2204"},[".title","Mene mene tekel upharsin"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mene-mene-tekel-upharsin.p1","order":".000.2205"},"The inscription interpreted by Daniel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/dan/5.25-28"},"Dan. 5:25–28"],"). It can be literally translated “numbered, numbered, weighed, and divisions.” Possibly the words are names of weights, “a mina, a mina, a shekel, and a half.” Daniel’s skill showed itself in his giving to these words an interpretation bearing on the circumstances of the time. In the interpretation (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/dan/5.28"},"verse 28"],")",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","peres"]],"is found instead of",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","upharsin."]],"The",["i","u"],"in",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","upharsin"]],"is simply “and.”",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","Parsin"]],"(which is written",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","pharsin"]],"when a vowel precedes) is the plural of",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","peres"]],"(pronounced so as to rhyme with",["i","deface"],").",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","Mene"]],"should be pronounced so as to rhyme with",["i","bewray,"],"and",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","tekel"]],"with",["i","bewail."]]]],"refs":null}
